TextEng: What are you, prisoner or guard?
Stand back! How do I know I can trust you?
Text: 물러서! 널 믿을 수 있다는 걸 내가 어떻게 알아?

TextEng: Relax - I set you free, didn't I?
What you be, huh? Pris'ner or guard guy?
Text: 너 뭐야, 응? 죄수야, 간수 놈이야?

TextEng: You stay back! How me trust you, huh?
Text: 뒤로 물러서! 나 너 어떻게 믿냐, 응?

TextEng: Huh? Me no cap-tor - me set you free!
Text: 어? 나 잡아 가둔 놈 아냐-내가 풀어줬지!

TextEng: Then I could use some information.
How did you end up in that cell in the first place?
Text: 처음에 어떻게 그 감방에 갇히게 된 거지?

TextEng: What's the layout of this floor?
Text: 이 층 구조가 어떻게 되어 있지?

TextEng: What do you know about the prisoners?
How you get 'prisoned anyway?
Think you can make your way out of here alone?
Any suggestions as to what we do now?
Text: 이제 어떻게 해야 할지 조언 있나?

TextEng: Okay, enough questions.
How dis place laid out?
What you know 'bout pris'ners?
What we do now?
Okay, questions all done.
Hmm. Me have questions.
You okay runnin' for door alone?
And the Head Gaoler?
<StartCheck>[Insight]</Start> The Pits? What's that?
And da Head Guy?
<StartCheck>[Insight]</Start> Did the Head Gaoler keep a logbook at all?
Okay, get out of here, then. I've cleared the way for you.
Text: 좋아, 그럼 여기서 나가. 길은 내가 닦아 놨어.

TextEng: Okay, you go now den. Me already clear path for you.
Text: 좋아, 이제 가. 내가 길 이미 치워놨어.

TextEng: I could use some information before you go.
